  <section>
    <h2>General Safety Expectations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>All staff must review and follow outlined safety policies.</li>
      <li>Report unsafe conditions immediately to Safety Support.</li>
      <li>Participate in regular drills and refresher trainings.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Behavioral Health Setting Considerations</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>De-escalation must be prioritized in all client interactions.</li>
      <li>Know trauma-informed practices and apply them consistently.</li>
      <li>Environmental safety checks should be performed daily.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Safety Support Roles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Act as a calm, trauma-informed safety presence on site.</li>
      <li>Assist with emergency situations and maintain site awareness.</li>
      <li>Work with supervisors to improve prevention planning.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Access Safety Resources</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Scan QR code on Safety Station posters.</li>
      <li>Visit the Safety Station website from your device.</li>
      <li>Check emergency binders at front desks.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
